33:30.116 --> 33:34.462
think that we could live through that. My concern 
would be that we'd get to the point someday, if you

33:35.343 --> 33:40.752
let your guard down. I mean, to me, you've got to try 
to save 100% of the trees on the block or the lot that

33:41.232 --> 33:47.802
you're working with. or you won't get them. If you 
try to save 100%, then you may get 50 or 60%. If you

33:54.985 --> 34:00.814
loosen your requirements and you say, well, let's 
strive for 50, you're going to get 25. And my real

34:01.576 --> 34:15.679
concern would be if we ever relaxed our rules, our 
demands on keeping the character of the forest,

34:01.576 --> 34:15.679
that forest is like people, like old people, If you 
just save the big trees, mature trees, you don't

34:16.233 --> 34:28.465
save all of the, to me it's understory and the 
shrubs, and we called it brush earlier, with the

34:16.233 --> 34:28.465
beauty part of the forest, and it's also where 
those child trees and the little trees are coming

34:16.233 --> 34:28.465
along. If you ever get to the point where you say, 
